{
  "stem": "21308.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it'd be the end of May, when the regiment was ordered home to reform in its true mountain role, to go to southeast Asia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we made our way back by road transport, right across Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- our last camp in Germany was a place called [NON-ENGLISH], near [NON-ENGLISH], in the Rhineland, where we were-- we were honored to be visited by our old CRA of the 52nd Scottish Division, who came and had a look at us and talked with us and told us things which we always knew but nobody ever told us, that we were quite the best in the British army.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we went, eventually, back to the north of Scotland, in Aberdeenshire, right up in the very north, a place called [INAUDIBLE] Camp, near Peterhead.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then from there, we went to Dingle, which is in Ross and Cromarty, in the north of the Highlands, to re-form.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we'd just got our first horses when the big bang happened over Hiroshima.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then Nagasaki.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Japanese emperor had enough sense to pull the plug.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then there was no need for it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so the regiment was disbanded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the whole rundown of the British army started.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had a release scheme.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I-- when the regiment was disbanded, I went back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went to Bochum.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I went, firstly, to the old German armored training area near Bad Lippspringe, with the artillery.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then I spent two years in Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My wife joined me in Rendsburg, on the Kiel Canal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was while I was at Rendsburg I got a visit by [NON-ENGLISH], who was the second in command to the Norwegians in Neustadt.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
